# SturdyEngine5 build requirements
# Info:
# - Configure from the repo root with the shared CMake presets.
# - Ninja is the supported generator because the project uses C++ modules.
# - Clang is the tested C++23 compiler path.
# Deps:
# - All platforms: CMake, Ninja, Clang, Vulkan SDK, Slang SDK.
# - Windows: MSBuild / Visual Studio Build Tools.
# - Linux: autogen/autotools.
# See docs/IDE_SETUP.md for the full setup notes.

# Version-control metadata
.lore/

# Build directories
build/
out/

# JetBrains CLion / IDE build trees and per-developer config.
# Shared .idea/ project files (runConfigurations/, vcs.xml) stay tracked; the
# per-developer ones are filtered by .idea/.gitignore. CLion's default out-of-source
# build dirs (used only if someone builds without the presets) are never shared.
/cmake-build-*/
# CMakeUserPresets.json holds a developer's own local presets; CMakePresets.json is
# the shared one. Keep user presets out of version control.
/CMakeUserPresets.json

# Stale/local root compile database files. The View As tasks point clangd directly
# at build/view/<os>/<profile>/compile_commands.json instead.
/compile_commands.json

# CMake generated files and directories
**/CMakeFiles/
**/CMakeCache.txt
**/CMakeConfigureLog.yaml
**/cmake_install.cmake
**/install_manifest.txt
**/CTestTestfile.cmake
**/CPackConfig.cmake
**/CPackSourceConfig.cmake
**/Makefile
**/build.ninja
**/.ninja_deps
**/.ninja_log
**/Testing/

# CMake FetchContent and external dependency build trees
**/_deps/
**/*-build/
**/*-subbuild/
**/*-populate-prefix/

# Compiler and linker outputs
*.o
*.obj
*.a
*.lib
*.so
*.so.*
*.dylib
*.dll
*.exe
*.pdb
*.ilk
*.d
*.gcda
*.gcno
*.gcov

# Runtime dumps and logs
*.log
*.dmp
*.core
core
